    "リコール開始": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Start Recall"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "何も見ずに思い出すことが、記憶を最も強くします。": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Recalling without looking strengthens memory the most."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "間違えても大丈夫！それが脳の成長のサインです。": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "It's okay to make mistakes! That's a sign of brain growth."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "復習は「読む」のではなく、「思い出す」のがコツ。": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "The trick to reviewing is not 'reading' but 'recalling'."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "エビングハウスの忘却曲線に打ち勝とう！": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Overcome Ebbinghaus's forgetting curve!"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "5分のリコールは、1時間の受動的な読書より効果的です。": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "A 5-minute recall is more effective than 1 hour of passive reading."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "「思い出そうとする時の負荷」が記憶を脳に定着させます。": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "The 'effort of trying to recall' anchors memories in the brain."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "少し忘れた頃に思い出すのが、最高のアクティブリコールです。": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Recalling when you've forgotten a little is the best active recall."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "インプット3割、アウトプット7割。これが学習の黄金比。": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Input 30%, Output 70%. This is the golden ratio of learning."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "完璧でなくてもOK。言葉を絞り出した数だけ定着します。": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "It's OK if it's not perfect. Every word you squeeze out anchors the memory."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "昨日の自分を超えるために、今日のリコールを始めましょう！": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Start your recall today to surpass who you were yesterday!"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "思い出す時に脳神経がつながります。頑張りどころです！": {
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Your neural network connects when you recall. This is where the effort pays off!"
          }
        }
      }
    },
